Date: Mon, 16 Jan 2012 12:41:47 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 0712/3390] USB: cdc-wdm: updating desc->length must be
 protected by spin_lock
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

commit c428b70c1e115c5649707a602742e34130d19428 upstream.

wdm_in_callback() will also touch this field, so we cannot change it without locking

Signed-off-by: Bj√∏rn Mork <bjorn@mork.no>
Acked-by: Oliver Neukum <oneukum@suse.de>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
---
 drivers/usb/class/cdc-wdm.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/class/cdc-wdm.c b/drivers/usb/class/cdc-wdm.c
index 2b9ff51..bac7478 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/class/cdc-wdm.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/class/cdc-wdm.c
@@ -467,7 +467,9 @@ retry:
 	for (i = 0; i < desc->length - cntr; i++)
 		desc->ubuf[i] = desc->ubuf[i + cntr];
 
+	spin_lock_irq(&desc->iuspin);
 	desc->length -= cntr;
+	spin_unlock_irq(&desc->iuspin);
 	/* in case we had outstanding data */
 	if (!desc->length)
 		clear_bit(WDM_READ, &desc->flags);
